  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 677 (sk3451): __getitem__, __setitem__, __delitem__ dict-presence checks for socket types."
    - "Theme: __getitem__/__setitem__/__delitem__ dict-presence (obj[key], obj[key]=val, del obj[key])."
    - "All values False — hashlib/uuid/struct/socket types do not implement container/mapping access protocols."
    - "socket.socket is a Python class; it does not define __getitem__, __setitem__, or __delitem__ in its __dict__."
    - "socket.AddressFamily and socket.SocketKind are IntEnum subclasses (EnumType metaclass)."
    - "AddressFamily and SocketKind are IntEnum but do NOT define __getitem__, __setitem__, or __delitem__ in their own __dict__; these methods are not overridden at the subclass level."
    - "operator.contains(socket.AddressFamily.__dict__, '__setitem__') is False — not present in AddressFamily's own __dict__."
    - "operator.contains(socket.SocketKind.__dict__, '__delitem__') is False — same reasoning as AddressFamily."
    - "All values are False for all 3 socket types across all 3 operators."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"
error_model: python_exceptions

